{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:galatians.6",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "galatians",
    "chapterNumber": 6,
    "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6",
    "summary": "Source text for Galatians 6 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.6.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:1",
      "text": "Brothers, even if a man is caught in some fault, you who are spiritual must restore such a one in a spirit of gentleness, looking to yourself so that you also aren’t tempted.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.6.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:2",
      "text": "Bear one another’s burdens, and so fulfill the law of Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.6.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:3",
      "text": "For if a man thinks himself to be something when he is nothing, he deceives himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.6.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:4",
      "text": "But let each man examine his own work, and then he will have reason to boast in himself, and not in someone else.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.6.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:5",
      "text": "For each man will bear his own burden.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.6.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:6",
      "text": "But let him who is taught in the word share all good things with him who teaches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.6.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:7",
      "text": "Don’t be deceived. God is not mocked, for whatever a man sows, that he will also reap.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.6.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:8",
      "text": "For he who sows to his own flesh will from the flesh reap corruption. But he who sows to the Spirit will from the Spirit reap eternal life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.6.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:9",
      "text": "Let’s not be weary in doing good, for we will reap in due season if we don’t give up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.6.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:10",
      "text": "So then, as we have opportunity, let’s do what is good toward all men, and especially toward those who are of the household of the faith.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.6.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:11",
      "text": "See with what large letters I write to you with my own hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.6.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:12",
      "text": "As many as desire to make a good impression in the flesh compel you to be circumcised, just so they may not be persecuted for the cross of Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.6.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:13",
      "text": "For even they who receive circumcision don’t keep the law themselves, but they desire to have you circumcised, so that they may boast in your flesh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.6.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:14",
      "text": "But far be it from me to boast except in the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ, through which the world has been crucified to me, and I to the world.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.6.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:15",
      "text": "For in Christ Jesus neither is circumcision anything, nor uncircumcision, but a new creation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.6.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:16",
      "text": "As many as walk by this rule, peace and mercy be on them, and on God’s Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.6.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:17",
      "text": "From now on, let no one cause me any trouble, for I bear the marks of the Lord Jesus branded on my body.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.6.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:18",
      "text": "The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit, brothers. Amen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
